I'd use helpers.get_param here.  It does all these checks already (isinstance, get_param, etc.) You can just call it on each value and look for one that returns "workload_context"

if any(get_param(val) == "workload_context" for val in metadata.values():
   if paramaters.get("workload_context", {}).get("type", "") != "string":
      return 'must have parameter "workload_context" of type "string"'
else:
   return None
